1.Update a bit ( to 1 or 0)
code:
 {
   ...>
   ...>
   ...>     Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
   ...>     int n = sc.nextInt();
   ...>
   ...>     int pos =2;
   ...>     int number= 0b0101,BitMask, NotBitMask, opr;
   ...>     if (n==1) {
    ...>         BitMask = 1<<pos;                     //set operation
   ...>         opr = BitMask | number;
   ...>         System.out.print(opr);
   ...>     }
   ...>     else {
   ...>         BitMask = 1<<pos;                     //clear operation 
   ...>         NotBitMask = ~(BitMask);
   ...>         opr = NotBitMask & number;
   ...>          System.out.print(opr);
   ...>     }
   ...> }
Output :
if 1 performs set operation and for 0 performs clear operation.

2. Get Bit at a given position
Code :

 {
   ...>     Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
   ...>     //int pos = sc.nextInt();
   ...>     int number = 5;
   ...>     int pos = 3;
   ...>     int BitMask, opr;
   ...>
   ...>     BitMask = 1<<pos;
   ...>     opr = BitMask & number;
   ...>     System.out.print(opr);
   } 
Output:
0

Q.3 Write a program to count the number of 1â€™s in a binary representation of the number.

Code:
 public class counts{
   ...>     public static void main ( String[]args){
   ...>         Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
  
   ...>          int n =sc.nextInt();
   ...>     int num=n;
   ...>         int count = countOnes(n);
   ...>
   ...>         System.out.print("Number of ones in binary representation :"+ count);
   ...>
   ...>     }
   ...>
   ...>     public  static int countOnes(int num) {
   ...>         int count =0;
   ...>    while(num != 0) {     count +=num & 1;
   ...>       num =  num >> 1;
   ...> }
   ...>
   ...>     return count;}
   ...> }
|  modified class counts

jshell> counts.main(null);
5
Number of ones in binary representation :2


Q.4) Write 2 functions => decimalToBinary() & binaryToDecimal() to convert a number from one number system to another. [BONUS]
Code :
 public class NumberConversion {
   ...>
   ...>         public static void main(String[] args) {
   ...>                 Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
   ...>
   ...>                 // Decimal to Binary
   ...>                 System.out.print("Enter decimal number: ");
   ...>                 int decimal = sc.nextInt();
   ...>                 System.out.println("Binary: " + decimalToBinary(decimal));
   ...>
   ...>                 // Binary to Decimal
   ...>                 System.out.print("Enter binary number: ");
   ...>                 String binary = sc.next();
   ...>                 System.out.println("Decimal: " + binaryToDecimal(binary));
   ...>         }
   ...>
   ...>         // Function to convert decimal to binary
   ...>         public static String decimalToBinary(int decimal) {
   ...>                 StringBuilder binary = new StringBuilder();
   ...>                 if (decimal == 0) return "0"; // Special case
   ...>                 while (decimal > 0) {
   ...>                         binary.insert(0, decimal % 2); // Add remainder at the front
   ...>                         decimal = decimal / 2;         // Divide by 2
   ...>                 }
   ...>                 return binary.toString();
   ...>         }
   ...>
   ...>         // Function to convert binary to decimal
   ...>         public static int binaryToDecimal(String binary) {
   ...>                 int decimal = 0;
   ...>                 int length = binary.length();
   ...>                 for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
   ...>                         if (binary.charAt(length - 1 - i) == '1') { // Rightmost bit first
   ...>                                 decimal += Math.pow(2, i);             // Add value to decimal
   ...>                         }
   ...>                 }
   ...>                 return decimal;
   ...>         }
   ...> }
|  created class NumberConversion

jshell> NumberConversion.main(null);
Enter decimal number: 12
Binary: 1100
Enter binary number: 1111
Decimal: 15


